Package: nle.api
Type: Package
Title: Neutral Sequence Model and Driver Dispatch for Non-Linear Editors
Version: 0.0.2.7
Date: 2026-06-04
Authors@R: c(
    person("Troy", "Hernandez", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "troy.h@cball.ai",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0005-4248-604X")),
    person("cornball.ai", role = "cph"))
Description: A neutral sequence model and driver dispatch layer for
    non-linear video editors. Defines a strict sequence schema, edit
    verbs that operate as pure functions on the sequence, and a driver
    registry so backend packages (e.g. blendR for Blender VSE, future
    drivers for ffmpeg, OTIO, FCP XML) can register dump and apply
    handlers. The canonical artifact is a Markdown file with a single
    delimited state block; a JSON companion is a generated cache.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Imports: jsonlite, Rcpp
LinkingTo: Rcpp
Suggests: tinytest
SystemRequirements: C++17, libopentimelineio (>= 0.17), built from source
    and installed under /usr/local (not available via apt; ships no
    pkg-config file). See PLAN.md for the build recipe.
